  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6593.87 sitting right between the massive negative gamma wall at 6590 (-12.1B) and positive gamma wall at 6605 (+14.3B), dealers are currently in amplification mode and likely buying this dip given we're just above the max negative gamma strike. The regime flip to BREAKOUT with -18.5B total GEX means dealers will chase momentum - they'll aggressively buy any move toward 6590 and aggressively sell any push through 6605, creating whipsaw conditions in this tight 15-point range. Key battle zone is 6590-6605 with additional amplification at 6580/6585 if we break lower.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect violent swings between 6590 and 6605 with big moves likely once either level breaks.",
